scrypt
------------------------------------------
The scrypt key derivation function was originally developed for use in the
Tarsnap online backup system and is designed to be far more secure against
hardware brute-force attacks than alternative functions such as PBKDF2 or
bcrypt.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libscrypt-kdf-devel-1.3.1-1bl1
  libscrypt-kdf1-1.3.1-1bl1
  libssl1.1-1.1.1f-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-7
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.tarsnap.com/scrypt.html

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Tarsnap/scrypt/archive/1.3.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack scrypt-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./scrypt-1.3.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/scrypt-1.3.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/scrypt-1.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt-kdf1-1.3.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt-kdf-devel-1.3.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(scrypt)
  /usr/bin/scrypt.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/scrypt.README
  /usr/share/doc/scrypt/Copyright
  /usr/share/doc/scrypt/FORMAT
  /usr/share/doc/scrypt/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/scrypt.1.gz

(libscrypt-kdf1)
  /usr/bin/cygscrypt-kdf-1.dll

(libscrypt-kdf-devel)
  /usr/include/scrypt-kdf.h
  /usr/lib/libscrypt-kdf.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/scrypt.pc

